> git status
> git clone <repo_link> <folder_name>
> git branch -b <branch_name>
> git config --global user.email "rohitnandi@sarathisoftech.com"
> git config --global user.name "rohitnandi"
> git config --global user.password "Rn@1205gh"

> git config --global credential.helper 'cache --timeout 3600'
Above command will tell git to cache your password for 1 hours.


> git credential-cache exit
How to make git forget this password ?
If you want to switch to another github account then u can run this command
Above command will flush any stored password from cache.


> git checkout -b <new_branch_name>  //create a new local branch
> git push -u origin <new_branch>	// -u is shortcut for --set-upstream
> git branch -a // show all branches
> git branch -r // show only remote branches
> git branch -d <branch_name>
> git branch -D <branch_name>  // force
> git push <remote_name> --delete <branch_name>

> git remote -v // view remote repositories linked to

